Innovation and Differentiators
What makes this solution unique?
This solution is unique because it treats MQ topology transformation as an architecture reasoning problem, not merely a CSV transformation or visualization problem.
It does not assume the input is clean. Instead, it explicitly models uncertainty, ambiguity, topology health, and data quality as first-class concerns.
Two differentiators
Differentiator 1: Explainable topology intelligence
The system not only produces a target topology, but also explains:
why a flow was kept
why it was changed
why it was excluded
where ambiguity exists
where manual review is justified
This makes the solution defensible in enterprise architecture review.
Differentiator 2: Hybrid automation + expert validation
The solution is automation-first, but it also supports structured expert override for high-risk cases. This is more realistic than a purely manual solution or a purely automated black box.
